Username Admin
Pass Admin
FORTI_HQ 1 ---> 192.168.1.201 (Secondary)          =============         FORTI_HQ2 ----> 192.168.1.200 (Primary)

1. Basic System Configuration
- Set hostname (FW-HQ-Primary)
- Configure admin password
- Set time zone and NTP servers
- Enable FortiGuard updates

2. Interface Configuration
-WAN Interface (port1): Public IP/DHCP, external connectivity
-LAN Interface (port2): Internal trusted network (10.5.0.0/16)
-HA Heartbeat (port3): Connection to secondary FortiGate
-Server VLAN Interface (port4): 172.16.10.0/24 network

3. Security Policies (Firewall Rules)
-WAN to LAN: Deny all (or restricted VPN access only)
-LAN to WAN: Outbound internet access (HTTP/HTTPS/DNS
-LAN to Servers: Permitted access to specific services
-Servers to LAN: Restricted/denied (servers shouldn't initiate connections to internal networks)

4. Network Address Translation (NAT)
-Source NAT: Internal to Internet

5. VPN Configuration
-Site-to-Site IPsec VPN: To all 4 branches (will be implemented in the Cisco Routers due to not having FortiGate firewalls on the branches.)
-SSL VPN: Remote access for employees

6. High Availability (HA)
-Configure an HA cluster with a secondary FortiGate
-Set HA mode (Active-Passive recommended)
-Configure the heartbeat interface and monitoring

7. Routing Configuration
-Static Routes: To internal networks (10.5.0.0/16, 172.16.10.0/24)
-OSPF: If using dynamic routing with an internal network

8. Security Services
-Antivirus: Enable scanning for HTTP, FTP, SMTP
-Intrusion Prevention (IPS): Enable with banking-specific profile
-Web Filtering: Restrict access to malicious categories
-Application Control: Block unwanted applications

9. Authentication
-Local Users/Groups: For admin access
-RADIUS Integration: With the AAA server (172.16.10.50)

10. Logging and Monitoring
-Configure syslog to the central server (172.16.10.60)
-Enable traffic logging for security policies
-Set up email alerts for critical events
